Sort prevalent virus/bacteria SGBs (100 samples) into temporal clusters with relative abundance

load packages

library(ggplot2)
library(data.table)
library(stringr)
library(dplyr)
library(tibble)
library(tidyr)
library(rprojroot)
library(cowplot)

Attaching package: cowplot

The following object is masked from package:ggpubr:

    get_legend
library(latrend)
library(nationalparkcolors)

set paths and filenames

### files
long_table=sprintf("%s/data/mp142_TGVG1.1_MPA4_combined_abundance_table_longform1.tsv", find_rstudio_root_file())
metadata_table=sprintf("%s/data/some_teddy_MP142_metadata2.all_samples1.delivery.csv", find_rstudio_root_file())

load long abundance table and metadata table, group abundance by SGBs

long_dt <- fread(sprintf("%s", long_table), sep = "\t", header = T) %>%
  mutate(species = gsub(".*s__","s__", lineage ), 
         genus = gsub(".*g__","g__", lineage ),
         sampleID = as.character(sampleID)) %>%
  mutate(genus = gsub("\\|s__.*", "", genus),
         kingdom = case_when(grepl("k__Bac", lineage) ~ "Bacteria", 
                           grepl("k__Vir", lineage) ~ "Virus",
                           grepl("k__Ar", lineage) ~ "Archea",
                           grepl("k__Euk", lineage) ~ "Eukaryota",
                           TRUE ~ "other")) %>%
  subset(select = c("rel_abundance", "sampleID", "species", "genus", "kingdom"))

prev_ab_dt <- long_dt %>%
  group_by(species) %>%
  ## 12,262 samples in TEDDY dataset, filter at 1%
  filter(n_distinct(sampleID) >= 100) %>%
  ungroup()

dim(
  prev_ab_dt %>% distinct(species)
)
[1] 1737    1
meta_dt <- fread(sprintf("%s", metadata_table), sep = ",", header = T) %>%
  select(-V1)

## this functions rounds a number up to the nearest 100
round_any = function(x, accuracy, f=ceiling){f(x/ accuracy) * accuracy}

prev_ab_meta_dt <- merge(prev_ab_dt, meta_dt, by.x = "sampleID", by.y = "sample") %>%
  mutate(rounded_DOL =  round_any(age_days, 100)) %>%
  filter(rounded_DOL <= 1400) %>%
  select(c(sampleID, species, rel_abundance, rounded_DOL)) %>%
  #group_by(species) %>%
  ## relative abundance in terms of the VC itself
  #mutate(self_rel_abund = rel_abundance / sum(rel_abundance)) %>%
  #ungroup() %>%
  group_by(species, rounded_DOL) %>%
  ## relative abundance to itself over all samples from each time bracket
  summarize(avg_rel_abund = mean(rel_abundance)) %>%
  mutate(self_rel_abund = avg_rel_abund / sum(avg_rel_abund)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  ## adding 0s for rounded_DOL where species was never detected
  complete(species, rounded_DOL) %>%
  replace(is.na(.), 0)
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'species'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

run latrend on prevalent SGBs

```r
#### run this for latrend
options(latrend.id = \species\, latrend.time = \rounded_DOL\)
plotTrajectories(prev_ab_meta_dt, response = \self_rel_abund\)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

prev_ab_meta_dt$assignment <- predictAssignments(kmlModelp, newdata = prev_ab_meta_dt)
prev_ab_meta_dt <- prev_ab_meta_dt %>% 
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'C', 'Subset 5'))  %>% 
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'F', 'Subset 1')) %>%
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'D', 'Subset 3'))  %>% 
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'E', 'Subset 2')) %>% 
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'A', 'Subset 4')) %>%
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'B', 'Subset 6')) %>%
  mutate(across('assignment', str_replace, 'G', 'Subset 7'))

king_gen_dt <- long_dt %>% 
  select(c(species, genus, kingdom)) %>% 
  distinct()
prev_ab_meta_dt <- merge(prev_ab_meta_dt, king_gen_dt, by = \species\)

```r
pal <- park_palette(\Arches\)
coul <- colorRampPalette(pal)(6)

linesp <- prev_ab_meta_dt %>%
  filter(kingdom == \Virus\) %>%
  group_by(assignment) %>%
  filter(n_distinct(species) > 10) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = rounded_DOL, y = self_rel_abund)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = species), color= \grey30\, alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = assignment), se = F) +
  scale_color_manual(values = coul) +
  facet_wrap(vars(assignment)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 0.3)) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = round(seq(min(prev_ab_meta_dt$rounded_DOL), 
                                        max(prev_ab_meta_dt$rounded_DOL), by = 200),1)) +
  labs(y = \Relative Abundance\, x = \Day of Life\) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1),
        legend.position = \Off\)
linesp
ggsave(linesp, file = sprintf(\%s/charts/virus_species_temporal_subsets_lines1.pdf\, find_rstudio_root_file()), width = 6, height = 5)

barsp <- prev_ab_meta_dt %>%
  filter(kingdom == \Virus\) %>%
  group_by(assignment) %>%
  filter(n_distinct(species) > 10) %>%
  summarize(clust_size = n_distinct(species)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = assignment, y = clust_size, fill = assignment)) +
  geom_col(color = \grey20\) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = coul) +
  labs(y = \Virus SGBs in Subset\) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank())
barsp
ggsave(barsp, file = sprintf(\%s/charts/virus_species_temporal_subsets_size1.pdf\, find_rstudio_root_file()), width = 3, height = 3)

```r
pal <- park_palette(\Arches\)
coul <- colorRampPalette(pal)(6)

linesp <- prev_ab_meta_dt %>%
  filter(kingdom == \Bacteria\) %>%
  group_by(assignment) %>%
  filter(n_distinct(species) > 10) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = rounded_DOL, y = self_rel_abund)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = species), color= \grey30\, alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = assignment), se = F) +
  scale_color_manual(values = coul) +
  facet_wrap(vars(assignment)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 0.3)) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = round(seq(min(prev_ab_meta_dt$rounded_DOL), 
                                        max(prev_ab_meta_dt$rounded_DOL), by = 200),1)) +
  labs(y = \Relative Abundance\, x = \Day of Life\) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1),
        legend.position = \Off\)
linesp
ggsave(linesp, file = sprintf(\%s/charts/bacteria_species_temporal_subsets_lines1.pdf\, find_rstudio_root_file()), width = 6, height = 5)

barsp <- prev_ab_meta_dt %>%
  filter(kingdom == \Bacteria\) %>%
  group_by(assignment) %>%
  filter(n_distinct(species) > 10) %>%
  summarize(clust_size = n_distinct(species)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = assignment, y = clust_size, fill = assignment)) +
  geom_col(color = \grey20\) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = coul) +
  labs(y = \Virus SGBs in Subset\) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank())
barsp
ggsave(barsp, file = sprintf(\%s/charts/bacteria_species_temporal_subsets_size1.pdf\, find_rstudio_root_file()), width = 3, height = 3)
